  <bodyText><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://cdn.inghams.co.uk/ImageGen.ashx?image=/media/9409535/03-northern-lights-harstad.jpg" alt="Island &amp; Fjord Adventure Checklist" /></p>
<ul>
<li>Warm clothing and layers – temperatures in Harstad average at approx. - 2° at this time of year, but can be varied, so it is important to have the right clothes to be as comfortable as possible during your trip, so we recommend thermals and winter jacket/salopettes if you have them. Layers are best as you will be going indoors to outdoors on some of the activities<br /><br /></li>
<li>Thermal suits and boots are provided on the RIB boat safari trip<br /><br /></li>
<li>Warm, sturdy footwear - there may be snow and ice on the ground at times, so make sure you bring sturdy comfortable and ideally waterproof shoes. If you feel more comfortable with crampons, please feel free to bring them although many places will request you remove them before venturing inside<br /><br /></li>
<li>Camera and tripod – essential for capturing great photos of the Northern Lights! Our guides on your Northern Lights Safari will be ready with tips<br /><br /></li>
<li>Binoculars – if you want to get a closer look at some of the wildlife on the RIB boat safari </li>
</ul>
